<div id="focusAndScope">
<h3>Focus and Scope&nbsp;</h3>
<p><em>Lenguaje</em>, published by the School of Language Sciences and sponsored by the Editorial Fund and the Vice-deanship of Research at Universidad del Valle, publishes works that fall within the area of language studies. It targets a readership of university professors, researchers and undergraduate and graduate students and it aims to be a space for sharing and disseminating experiences and reflection about language studies.</p>
<p><em>Lenguaje</em>&nbsp;publishes papers in all disciplines dealing with language, mainly in the areas of linguistics and language teaching (education), either in the form of papers (reports of original research or research in progress, academic essays, review articles over a subject matter, reviews of a particular problem, systematic reports of educational experiences) or in the form of book reviews. The opinions expressed by the authors do not necessarily reflect the point(s) of view of the editorial board.</p>
<p>The journal is indexed in the Publindex National Bibliographic Database Colciencias in category C. it is also indexed in the following international bibliographic databases CSA Linguistics and Language Behavior Abstracts (BALF), Ulrich\'s Periodical Director, SciELO Colombia, MLA International Bibliography and Academic Report ─ in the last two,&nbsp;<em>in extenso</em>.</p>
<p><strong>Periodicity</strong></p>
<p>Since 2007,&nbsp;<em>Lenguaje</em>&nbsp;publishes two issues a year: one in January and one in July.</p>
<p><strong>Statement of Publication Ethics and Publication Malpractice</strong></p>
<p>This policy of ethics and good editorial practices is intended to serve as a code of conduct for all those involved in the processes of review and submission of original research, essays, reviews and other publications for the journal&nbsp;<em>Lenguaje</em>: editorial board, peer reviewers, authors and editorial board.</p>
<p><strong>Responsibilities of the Editor in chief</strong></p>
<p>The editor of the journal&nbsp;<em>Lenguaje</em>&nbsp;is responsible for:</p>
<p><strong><em>Decision-making</em></strong>: the editor, along with the Editorial Board, should make decisions on whether or not to accept a manuscript on the grounds of editorial standards of the journal. Under no circumstances commercial, economic, academic, or personal biases should prevail in this decision-making process.</p>
<p><strong><em>Integrity of the process and transparency in the information provided</em></strong>: the editor, as well as the members of the editorial and scientific committees, must ensure compliance with editorial standards by the authors as well as the promptitude and objectivity in the evaluations by peer reviewers. If any of the parties involved in the submission and review processes is affected by any conflict of interest, the person shall refrain him/herself from participating.</p>
<p><strong><em>Promoting a process of profitable writing for authors and peer reviewers</em></strong><strong>:</strong>&nbsp;under the premise that writing and knowledge are built and consolidated through a constant dialogue between academic peers, the editor will always ensure the provision of data and indications to comply with that premise. The editor must also respond effectively and promptly to the concerns, suggestions or comments from authors and peer reviewers.</p>
<p><strong><em>Preserving the anonymity of the authors and peer reviewers</em></strong>: through the double-blind peer-review process, the publisher shall ensure objectivity and impartiality from both reviewers and authors.</p>
<p><strong><em>Avoiding plagiarism and self-plagiarism</em></strong>: the editor will verify the originality of all manuscripts submitted for publication using specialized software to detect plagiarism. The journal&nbsp;<em>Lenguaje</em>&nbsp;herein states its commitment to the respect and integrity of the rights held by authors of published research. Plagiarism and self-plagiarism will not be tolerated and any manuscript found to have reproduced partially or totally formerly published works without the due authorization or citation will automatically be rejected. In the event that plagiarism is detected after the publication of a paper even after its originality was checked during the editing process, the journal will publish a special notice censoring the published article in the next printed issue. The journal&nbsp;<em>Lenguaje</em>&nbsp;states that the content of the articles is the sole responsibility of the authors which also applies in cases of plagiarism and self-plagiarism.</p>
<p><strong>Responsibilities of peer reviewers</strong></p>
<p>The peer reviewers of the journal&nbsp;<em>Lenguaje</em>&nbsp;should commit to:</p>
<p><strong><em>Avoiding conflict of interest with any research, author (s) or other persons or institutions involved in financing the research:</em></strong>&nbsp;in case of any conflict of interest with either party involved in the review and publication of articles, the affected party shall refrain from participating. Therefore, the entire editorial staffs, as well as the editor of the journal, ensure the objectivity of all judgments issued by the peer reviewers.</p>
<p><em><strong>Confidentiality of information</strong></em>: peer reviewers shall not share or use information from one part or all of a manuscript for their own benefit or that of third parties.</p>
<p><strong><em>Complying to evaluate a manuscript after acceptance</em></strong>: it is expected that the reviewer, if possible, meets deadlines. The Journal&nbsp;<em>Lenguaje</em>&nbsp;does not grant financial compensation for the evaluation of manuscripts; in return, the reviewers receive two print copies of the issue in which the reviewed article is published.</p>
<p><strong>Responsibilities of authors</strong></p>
<p>All authors who submit a paper to the journal&nbsp;<em>Lenguaje</em>&nbsp;are committed to:</p>
<p><em><strong>Adherening to the editorial standards of the journal</strong></em>: Authors must be familiar and fully comply with the editorial standards of the journal, as published on the journal’s website, and this statement of ethics. By submitting a manuscript, authors accept the terms and policies that rule the journal standards. Thus authors must guarantee that the submitted manuscript and all associated materials are original and do not infringe copyright laws national nor international. In the case of multiple-author manuscripts, all authors shall make explicit their full consensus and that the submitted manuscript has not been previously published or submitted for review in other journal print or otherwise.</p>
<p><em><strong>Submitting a Journal Publishing Agreement</strong></em>: Upon pre-acceptance of a manuscript, authors will be asked to complete a \'Journal Publishing Agreement\' (available in the journal’s website) by which they certify the veracity and authenticity of the information and data the article presents. Authors must also explicitly authorize the journal to publish, edit, partially or fully reproduce and disclose their work -nationally or internationally-through print or electronic media (web, databases, etc.).</p>
<p><strong><em>Correcting mistakes</em></strong>: Authors are required to actively participate in the review process by making all suggested changes and revisions peer evaluators make about their work. Once both written reviews are sent to the authors, they are also requested to submit, along with the second version, a document in which they show which suggestions and changes were adopted and which ones were not, including a justification in the latter.</p>
<p><strong><em>Acting as reviewer</em></strong>: once a paper is published in the journal, the respective authors enter into the database of possible peer reviewer for future manuscripts in their corresponding area of expertise. Mutual and selfless collaboration of authors as future reviewers is taken for granted as a result of publication of their manuscripts.</p>
<p><strong>Responsibilities of the editorial board</strong></p>
<p>The editorial board is made up of the editorial and the scientific committees. The boards works jointly with the chief editor in the following aims:</p>
<p>- Maintain the integrity of the publication.</p>
<p>- Ensure that the journal’s editorial standards are fully met.</p>
<p>- Observing the code of ethics and publishing malpractices.</p>
<p>- Disclose any potential conflicts of interest regarding any submitted work.</p>
<p>-To identify potential instances of plagiarism and self-plagiarism, and promptly report them to the chief editor.&nbsp;</p>
</div>
